OL,3,CBurnham confirms he won't accept a
OL,4,Ccabinet job in Starmer's government
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer told ITV News his
OL,7,Fgovernment is just two years into its
OL,8,Ffive-year mandate, and that he remains
OL,9,F'motivated only to serve', as
OL,10,FPolitical Editor Robert Peston reports
OL,12,FSir Keir Starmer said if Labour wins
OL,13,FMakerfield, he would offer Andy
OL,14,FBurnham a cabinet job and said "I want
OL,15,Fhim to have a big role in government".
OL,17,FBurnham has since confirmed he will
OL,18,Fnot be taking any government role that
OL,19,Fmay be offered to him by Starmer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
