OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1781894898
OL,3,CBurnham confirms he won't accept a
OL,4,Ccabinet job in Starmer's government
OL,6,FIf he returns to Westminster as an MP,
OL,7,FBurnham is widely expected to
OL,8,Fchallenge Starmer for leadership and
OL,9,Fcould trigger a contest as early as
OL,10,FFriday.
OL,12,FEarlier on Wednesday, the PM warned
OL,13,FBurnham against launching an immediate
OL,14,Fleadership challenge, instead asking
OL,15,Fhim and the Labour party to focus on
OL,16,Fthe election of a new Greater
OL,17,FManchester Mayor.
OL,19,FSpeaking to journalists at the G7
OL,20,Fsummit, Starmer warned Burnham to not
OL,21,Fchallenge him for leadership.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1781894898
OL,3,CBurnham confirms he won't accept a
OL,4,Ccabinet job in Starmer's government
OL,6,FHe said that if Burnham wins the
OL,7,FMakerfield by-election, his focus
OL,8,Fshould instead be on helping the party
OL,9,Fwin the Manchester mayoralty again,
OL,10,Fcalling it "one of the biggest by-
OL,11,Felections that we've ever fought".
OL,13,FA by-election for the mayoralty would
OL,14,Flikely to be at the start of August.
OL,16,FStarmer said: "It's really important
OL,17,Fto my mind that the whole of the
OL,18,FLabour Party and Labour movement
OL,19,Ffocuses on that, which is the next
OL,20,Fmost immediate task."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1781894898
OL,3,CBurnham confirms he won't accept a
OL,4,Ccabinet job in Starmer's government
OL,6,FThe PM told reporters that "first and
OL,7,Fforemost, I want Andy Burnham to win",
OL,8,Fbut made it clear he did not want that
OL,9,Fvictory to spark a leadership
OL,10,Fchallenge.
OL,12,FHe said: "I don't think there should
OL,13,Fbe a challenge.
OL,15,F"I think history, particularly the
OL,16,Flast government, shows that that isn't
OL,17,Fa successful way for a government to
OL,18,Fbehave."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
